caption: Absolutely the best poke spot! I tried Ono Seafood and couple more, this is just the best. I ate there at least 7 times during my trip.

Really yummy poke! Lots of sauce and fish variety to pick from, and white brown or sushi rice. Serve time is pretty fast given the demand for their foods. Note that they often will run out of supply, and may even have to close early, so try not to miss the closing time. I would eat here regularly!  Not related to Maguro Bros ("maguro" just means "tuna" apparently).

Best Poke spot! Their Blue Marlin and Tuna fish come fresh every morning from local fisherman! Yuki the owner a young guy is very kind and helpful. They have the best value and quality I’ve seen in Poke so I will keep coming back! Poke bowls range from s-xl small starting at $8 and xl at $18.  Also make sure to hit the water afterwards and rent some boards from Moku Hawaii as they are the best shop and also are related to this poke spot! Mahalo Maguro Spot!

Loved this place and was so sad that we only found it on our last day.  By far the best Poke bowl we ate on Oahu. The young owner was super enthusiastic and helpful.  It is definitely more of a hole in the wall with just a couple of tables on the sidewalk.  However, it is a short walk from the beautiful beaches so buy to go and walk to the beach!  Highly recommend.
Rainbow poke bowl is Wonderful! Sushi rice and edamame so good!
The best poke, great people, great vibes. Such great value and flavor - we ate here every day of our vacation. Also so close to the beach you can grab and go!
Must stop for poke.
The best in Honolulu!
Tiny hole in the wall with pretty good food. They have a variety of sauces and added sea vegetables to the bowls. The bowls were pretty unique and I like any I’ve had before.
Wonderful Poke Bowl. Build it yourself.  I'll be going back!
My favorite spot! I literally came here every day. The poke is amazing and the people are lovely! 🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻🤩
Probably the best Poke I've ever had. Highly recommend the Salmon w/ Spicy Mayo & Teriyaki, edamame and seaweed.
Nice, fresh, poke spot near the busy area.
Love this place. I go as often as possible 😋 the poke is delicious and staff is really nice!
The two times we’ve been here, they don’t have what we want!
Good low-key spot for quality poke. Staff are great, and the service is quick. I keep finding myself in this place.
Great Poke. Great Service. Prices are reasonable for the quality. Definitely recommend!

Most of my reviews are for Celiacs (gluten free) Nice place to go for poke.  However just one option is available for celiacs.  That is the Hawaiian style.  All they offer is a GF soy sauce no other sauces are GF.  The tuna bowl was delicious with the added avocado.

Busy little poke spot. Unfortunately they are very limited with gluten free options. The only thing the staff said was safe was the original Hawaiian style poke bowl or a veggie bowl. Yes they do have gluten free soy sauce but no longer have gluten free shoyu sauce. The spicy poke wasn’t gluten free either sadly. On a positive note the tuna was extremely fresh and all the ingredients were tasty! So knocking it one star for lack of options, however keeping it a 4 star rating because the quality of the bowl was fantastic.
my husband discovered this place. and it's my favorite poke spot in waikiki. all fresh and delicious! recommended to everybody I know
Excellent customer service and the food fantastic....   ordered a veggie bowl Will definitely be back

Amazing poke! We came back nearly every day since discovering this place - great value/cheap for Hawaii, fresh meal with amazing taste. Happy for this discovery! We would get  medium bowl with #9 creamy sesame salmon/sushi rice, sooo good, I am salivating while describing it. Would definitely recommend! If you like sushi/poke you will not regret    eating here! One table with 2 seats available outside to enjoy your meal.

A lot of missing ingredients (which were extras), no sauces and they didn't even give us the sushi rice we ordered but instead gave us white rice and a lot of onion. I don't know how you can have any excuse or get away with that many mistakes in one order with very little people coming into your shop. Wish I checked our order prior to catching the bus. I think we put too much trust on these kids.

Also very expensive compared to other poke places I’ve been to that have just as fresh fish but you get a lot more poke for you money. Had to supplement my poke bowl with an ala carte order of just poke which was another $7.00 on top of my $8.50 poke bowl with $2 extra dollars because they gave me a lil spoon or avacado and a little spoon of tobiko.  I don’t mind paying for good quality but it was just ok and nickel and diming everything with small portion sizes is not that good! Overpriced I woood find other better value poke spots in Waikiki

POKE! No longer is the day that I have nowhere to recommend people staying in Waikiki of a good spot to get poke!  Run by the same Japanese family that owns the famous MOKU surf shop located right up towards the beach.  This new small but excellent poke shop serves up fresh Ahi or Maguro in Japanese or Salmon.  The flavors are plentiful, and on my first experience to Maguro Spot I got the Spicy Sesame and my girlfriend ate the spicy Ahi.  Both were spectacular!  If there is one thing you should know about Japanese running a business that has to do with fish and rice, ... (well I'm sure it's pretty obvious... but I'll point it out anyway) they take it very seriously.  Rice is the main staple of Japan and if you mess that up, say goodbye to your Japanese customers.  So your base of rice is covered, check that one off the list and know that the one ingredient you weren't even thinking about is already getting umami flavors flowing before you even know it.  OK, lets move on to the Ahi, which is the core of this dish.  My girlfriend pointed out that even the shape and size of the poke was excellent, and not too big.  The freshness of the Maguro really comes out to me when it's put on top of warm rice.  I added avocado because I like that combo, and along with the spicy sesame it was super ONO! (delicious)
